  "bib_entries": {
    "27688082": {
      "title": "Kernel and fast algorithm for dense triplet inconsistency",
      "abstract": "We study the parameterized complexity of inferring supertrees from sets of rooted triplets, an important problem in phylogenetics. For a set L of labels and a dense set T of triplets distinctly leaf-labeled by 3-subsets of L, we seek a tree distinctly leaf-labeled by L and containing all but at most k triplets from T as homeomorphic subtree. Our results are the first polynomial kernel for this problem, with O(k^2) labels, and a subexponential fixed-parameter algorithm running in time O(|L|^4)+2^O^(^k^^^1^^^/^^^3^l^o^g^k^)."
